# Heart Disease Prediction App

This is a full-stack machine learning app for predicting heart disease risk. It includes a Python backend for model inference and a frontend built with modern JavaScript tooling (Vite + pnpm).

---

## Quickstart: Local Setup

This guide walks you through setting up the project on a fresh machine.

---

### Requirements

- [Node.js 16.9+](https://nodejs.org/en/download/)
- (only for mac) [Corepack (comes with Node 16.9+)](https://nodejs.org/api/corepack.html)

---

## 1. Clone the Repo and Switch to `master` Branch

git clone https://github.com/ChicoState/heartdisease.git

cd heartdisease

git checkout master

cd hdrd


#### Chained Command : 
#### git clone https://github.com/ChicoState/heartdisease.git && cd heartdisease && git checkout master && cd hdrd

---

# 2. Set Up Python Backend

> Create a virtual environment and install backend dependencies.

## Python Version Compatibility


### Install Python 3.9 (or later)


###### For macOS (with Homebrew):
brew install python@3.9

###### For Linux (with apt):
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y python3.9 python3.9-venv python3.9-dev

### Verify installation

python3.9 --version

#### Should show Python 3.9.x or higher (optional)

brew link python@3.9 --force --overwrite

#### Chained Command : 
#### Mac: brew install python@3.9 && python3.9 --version && brew link python@3.9 --force --overwrite
#### Linux: sudo apt update && sudo apt install python3.9 python3.9-venv python3.9-dev && python3.9 --version

---

# 3. Create a virtual environment using Python 3.9
python3.9 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

### Upgrade pip to the latest version
pip install --upgrade pip

### Install the required Python dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt


#### Chained Command : 
#### python3.9 -m venv venv && source venv/bin/activate && pip install --upgrade pip && pip install -r requirements.txt

---

## 3. Set Up Frontend with pnpm

> ( only for Mac ) We use `pnpm` (a fast Node.js package manager), managed through Corepack so users don't need global installs.

### Enable Corepack: ( only for Mac )
corepack enable

### Install dependencies:
pnpm install

### Start the frontend dev server:
pnpm dev

> This will start the frontend on [http://localhost:3000]


#### Chained Command : 
#### corepack enable && pnpm install && pnpm dev

---

## You're all set!

Your app should now be running locally.

---